@startuml
package "System Monitor Application" {
  [CLI Interface] as CLI
  [TUI Interface] as TUI
  [REST API] as API
  [Core Monitor Engine] as Core
  [Data Models] as Models
  [Database Layer] as DB
  [Configuration] as Config
}

package "External Systems" {
  [Operating System\n(sysinfo, psutil)] as OS
  [PostgreSQL Database] as PostgreSQL
  [HTTP Clients] as HTTP
  [Terminal/Console] as Terminal
}

CLI -down-> Core
TUI -down-> Core
API -down-> Core
Core -right-> Models
Core -down-> DB
Core -left-> Config

Core .u.> OS : reads system info
DB .u.> PostgreSQL : stores/retrieves data
TUI .u.> Terminal : renders interface
API .u.> HTTP : serves requests

note right of Core
  Main monitoring logic:
  - system_monitor::services
  - Real-time data collection
  - Caching and aggregation
end note

note left of Models
  Data structures:
  - SystemMetrics
  - ProcessInfo  
  - TemperatureInfo
  - Serialization/Deserialization
end note
@enduml